The paper investigates the use and impact of arXiv e-prints in various fields, including physics, mathematics, astronomy, and astrophysics. While the paper does not focus specifically on computer science, it does mention the use of arXiv in the field and the analysis of data from the entirety of arXiv, which includes several computer science sub-categories. The sub-categories listed above are the most likely based on the content of the paper and the fields it covers. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are relevant due to the focus on the use and dissemination of research. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible due to the broader interdisciplinary nature of the paper. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possibility due to the analysis of citation patterns and impact.
